abstract: Being crowned world champions should be the ultimate incentive in any sport, but Liverpool manager Juergen Klopp knows that when it comes to club football, Europe does not see it that way.
snippet: Being crowned world champions should be the ultimate incentive in any sport, but Liverpool manager Juergen Klopp knows that when it comes to club football, Europe does not see it that way.
lead_paragraph: DOHA — Being crowned world champions should be the ultimate incentive in any sport, but Liverpool manager Juergen Klopp knows that when it comes to club football, Europe does not see it that way.
headline_main: Liverpool's Klopp Wants Only to Win as Flamengo Chase Hero Status
headline_print_headline: Liverpool's Klopp Wants Only to Win as Flamengo Chase Hero Status

abstract: The Carnival Glory crashed into the Carnival Legend while “maneuvering to dock” in Cozumel, Mexico, a spokeswoman for the cruise line said.
snippet: The Carnival Glory crashed into the Carnival Legend while “maneuvering to dock” in Cozumel, Mexico, a spokeswoman for the cruise line said.
lead_paragraph: One Carnival cruise ship crashed into another while trying to dock at a port in Mexico on Friday, leaving six injured passengers, a damaged hull and a handful of expletive-laden social media videos in its wake.

abstract: Chinese President Xi Jinping, in a call with President Donald Trump on Friday, accused the United States of interfering in its internal affairs but expressed hope that the two leaders could keep lines of communication open, China's Xinhua news agency said.
snippet: Chinese President Xi Jinping, in a call with President Donald Trump on Friday, accused the United States of interfering in its internal affairs but expressed hope that the two leaders could keep lines of communication open, China's Xinhua news age...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Chinese President Xi Jinping, in a call with President Donald Trump on Friday, accused the United States of interfering in its internal affairs but expressed hope that the two leaders could keep lines of communication open, China's Xinhua news agency said.
headline_main: China's Xi, in Call With Trump, Says U.S. Interfering in Its Affairs: Xinhua
headline_print_headline: China's Xi, in Call With Trump, Says U.S. Interfering in Its Affairs: Xinhua

abstract: United Airlines Holdings Inc said on Friday it is extending cancellations of Boeing 737 MAX flights from early March until June 4, the longest that any U.S. carrier is scheduling without the grounded aircraft.
snippet: United Airlines Holdings Inc said on Friday it is extending cancellations of Boeing 737 MAX flights from early March until June 4, the longest that any U.S. carrier is scheduling without the grounded aircraft.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO/WASHINGTON — United Airlines Holdings Inc said on Friday it is extending cancellations of Boeing 737 MAX flights from early March until June 4, the longest that any U.S. carrier is scheduling without the grounded aircraft.
headline_main: United Airlines Pulls Boeing 737 MAX Jets Until Early June
headline_print_headline: United Airlines Pulls Boeing 737 MAX Jets Until Early June

abstract: Fiat Chrysler will stick to its 5 billion euro (£4.25 billion) 2020 investment plan for Italy, union officials said on Friday, adding that the group had confirmed a pledge to get all employees off furlough arrangements and back to work by 2022.
snippet: Fiat Chrysler will stick to its 5 billion euro (£4.25 billion) 2020 investment plan for Italy, union officials said on Friday, adding that the group had confirmed a pledge to get all employees off furlough arrangements and back to work by 2022.
lead_paragraph: TURIN, Italy — Fiat Chrysler will stick to its 5 billion euro (£4.25 billion) 2020 investment plan for Italy, union officials said on Friday, adding that the group had confirmed a pledge to get all employees off furlough arrangements and back to work by 2022.
headline_main: FCA Sticks to Investment Plan for Italy, No Redundancies-Unions
headline_print_headline: FCA Sticks to Investment Plan for Italy, No Redundancies-Unions

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump spoke on Friday with Chinese President Xi Jinping and claimed progress on issues from trade to North Korea and Hong Kong, but China said Xi accused the United States of interfering in its internal affairs.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump spoke on Friday with Chinese President Xi Jinping and claimed progress on issues from trade to North Korea and Hong Kong, but China said Xi accused the United States of interfering in its internal affairs.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON/BEIJING — U.S. President Donald Trump spoke on Friday with Chinese President Xi Jinping and claimed progress on issues from trade to North Korea and Hong Kong, but China said Xi accused the United States of interfering in its internal affairs.
headline_main: In Phone Call With Trump, China's Xi Says U.S. Interfering in Internal Affairs
headline_print_headline: In Phone Call With Trump, China's Xi Says U.S. Interfering in Internal Affairs

abstract: Five historians wrote to us with their reservations. Our editor in chief replies.
snippet: Five historians wrote to us with their reservations. Our editor in chief replies.
lead_paragraph: The letter below will be published in the Dec. 29 issue of The New York Times Magazine. RE: The 1619 ProjectWe write as historians to express our strong reservations about important aspects of The 1619 Project. The project is intended to offer a new version of American history in which slavery and white supremacy become the dominant organizing themes. The Times has announced ambitious plans to make the project available to schools in the form of curriculums and related instructional material.
headline_main: Letter to the Editor: Historians Critique The 1619 Project, and We Respond

abstract: France's CGT oil sector workers union plans to step up a nationwide strike but will leave the decision over whether to halt production at refineries for workers to decide early next week, a CGT union official said.
snippet: France's CGT oil sector workers union plans to step up a nationwide strike but will leave the decision over whether to halt production at refineries for workers to decide early next week, a CGT union official said.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — France's CGT oil sector workers union plans to step up a nationwide strike but will leave the decision over whether to halt production at refineries for workers to decide early next week, a CGT union official said.
headline_main: France's CGT Oil Workers Could Halt Refinery Production Over Pensions Reform
headline_print_headline: France's CGT Oil Workers Could Halt Refinery Production Over Pensions Reform

abstract: Montenegro, which is hoping to find oil and gas reserves off its coast, said on Friday it has extended Energean Oil & Gas's licence by a year to explore two blocks as the Greek company required more time.
snippet: Montenegro, which is hoping to find oil and gas reserves off its coast, said on Friday it has extended Energean Oil & Gas's licence by a year to explore two blocks as the Greek company required more time.
lead_paragraph: SARAJEVO — Montenegro, which is hoping to find oil and gas reserves off its coast, said on Friday it has extended Energean Oil & Gas's licence by a year to explore two blocks as the Greek company required more time.
headline_main: Energean Gets Extra Year to Explore Montenegro's Offshore Oil and Gas Blocks
headline_print_headline: Energean Gets Extra Year to Explore Montenegro's Offshore Oil and Gas Blocks

abstract: A Connecticut city will pay $5 million to the family of a teenage girl stabbed to death at her high school to settle a lawsuit alleging the district did not properly respond to threats posed by the killer, attorneys for the plaintiffs said Friday.
snippet: A Connecticut city will pay $5 million to the family of a teenage girl stabbed to death at her high school to settle a lawsuit alleging the district did not properly respond to threats posed by the killer, attorneys for the plaintiffs said Friday....
lead_paragraph: MILFORD, Conn. — A Connecticut city will pay $5 million to the family of a teenage girl stabbed to death at her high school to settle a lawsuit alleging the district did not properly respond to threats posed by the killer, attorneys for the plaintiffs said Friday.
headline_main: City to Pay $5M to Settle Lawsuit Over Fatal School Stabbing
headline_print_headline: City to Pay $5M to Settle Lawsuit Over Fatal School Stabbing
